=head1 DESCRIPTION

Describes the state of the name server records update made by Amazon
Lightsail to an Amazon Route 53 registered domain.

For more information, see DNS in Amazon Lightsail
(https://docs.aws.amazon.com/lightsail/latest/userguide/understanding-dns-in-amazon-lightsail)
in the I<Amazon Lightsail Developer Guide>.

=head1 ATTRIBUTES


=head2 Code => Str

The status code for the name servers update.

Following are the possible values:

=over

=item *

C<SUCCEEDED> - The name server records were successfully updated.

=item *

C<PENDING> - The name server record update is in progress.

=item *

C<FAILED> - The name server record update failed.

=item *

C<STARTED> - The automatic name server record update started.

=back



=head2 Message => Str

The message that describes the reason for the status code.



